			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">The average labor refers to the average work time and wage of workers. According to the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics, as of December 2020, the average hourly wage of United States citizens is 29.81,andtheaverageweeklywageis1034.41. This is a 4.8% increase from December 2019. The average hours worked per week in the U.S. was 38.7 hours as of 2021. Men worked an average of 40.5 hours per week, while women worked 36.6 hours per week.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">平均劳动力是指工人的平均工作时间和工资。根据美国劳工统计局的数据，截至 2020 年 12 月，美国公民的平均时薪为 29.81 美元，平均周薪为 1034.41 美元。这比 2019 年 12 月增长了 4.8%。截至 2021 年，美国每周平均工作时间为 38.7 小时。男性每周平均工作 40.5 小时，女性每周平均工作 36.6 小时。</common:generalComment>
